Here's a refactor proposal that ties each change to the finding it resolves.

## Refactored `src/Card.tsx`

```tsx
import styles from "./Card.module.css";

type CardProps = {
  children: React.ReactNode;
  sidebar?: React.ReactNode;
  onActivate?: () => void;
  label?: string;
};

export function Card({ children, sidebar, onActivate, label }: CardProps) {
  const interactive = Boolean(onActivate);

  // Accessible_interaction_risk (crime_00001):
  // promote the clickable wrapper to a real <button> when it has behaviour.
  // Non-interactive cards stay as a <section> with no click handler at all.
  if (interactive) {
    return (
      <button
        type="button"
        className={styles.card}
        onClick={onActivate}
        aria-label={label}
      >
        <CardBody sidebar={sidebar}>{children}</CardBody>
      </button>
    );
  }

  return (
    <section className={styles.card} aria-label={label}>
      <CardBody sidebar={sidebar}>{children}</CardBody>
    </section>
  );
}

function CardBody({
  children,
  sidebar,
}: {
  children: React.ReactNode;
  sidebar?: React.ReactNode;
}) {
  return (
    <div className={styles.body}>
      <div className={styles.content}>{children}</div>
      {sidebar ? <aside className={styles.sidebar}>{sidebar}</aside> : null}
    </div>
  );
}
```

## Companion `src/Card.module.css`

```css
/* design_token_escape (crime_00002):
   every literal comes from the token layer — `var(--color-surface)` etc.
   Agents extending the file inherit the tokens by default. */
.card {
  background: var(--color-surface-accent);
  color: var(--color-on-surface);
  border: 1px solid var(--color-border-subtle);
  border-radius: var(--radius-md);
  box-shadow: var(--shadow-1);
  outline-color: var(--color-focus-ring);
  padding: var(--space-6);

  /* responsive_fragility (crime_00003):
     fluid width with a ceiling, fluid type with clamp(),
     and a layout that collapses on small viewports. */
  width: 100%;
  max-width: 64rem;
}

.body {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1fr) 15rem;
  gap: var(--space-4);
}

.content {
  font-size: clamp(1rem, 0.9rem + 0.4vw, 1.125rem);
}

.sidebar {
  font-size: var(--font-size-sm);
  color: var(--color-on-surface-muted);
}

@media (max-width: 48rem) {
  .body {
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
  }
}
```

## How each change maps back to the findings

| Finding | Fix | Why this answers it |
|---|---|---|
| `accessible_interaction_risk` (line 10) | The clickable wrapper becomes a real `<button type="button">` with `aria-label` when `onActivate` is passed; the non-interactive path is a `<section>`. The stray `console.log` `onClick` is gone — no more "div with a click handler." | Native focus, keyboard activation (`Enter`/`Space`), and screen-reader semantics come for free. No bolt-on `role="button"` / `tabIndex={0}` / key handler is needed. |
| `design_token_escape` (9 raw values on lines 10–24) | Inline `style={…}` is replaced with a CSS module that references `var(--color-…)`, `var(--space-…)`, `var(--radius-…)`, `var(--shadow-…)`. | Agents extending `Card.tsx` now see token names, not hex/rgb literals, so they can't accidentally copy `#ff00aa` forward. |
| `responsive_fragility` (lines 12, 14, 24, no `@media`) | `width: 800` and `width: 720` → `width: 100%` + `max-width: 64rem` plus a `minmax(0, 1fr) 15rem` grid. `fontSize: 18` → `clamp(1rem, 0.9rem + 0.4vw, 1.125rem)`. A single `@media (max-width: 48rem)` collapses the grid. | Fixed pixel widths and at least one fixed font size are gone, and the file finally has a `@media` rule — directly matching the detector's "no `@media` query in the file" evidence string. |

## Bonus knock-on wins (not required, called out so the detector deltas are predictable)

- Inline `style=` is fully removed, so a future `crimes scan` should drop `design_token_escape` to zero hard-coded values rather than just reducing the count.
- The `<div>` with `onClick` no longer exists, so `accessible_interaction_risk` should disappear entirely — not just have aria patched onto it.
- `outlineColor` is now a token (`--color-focus-ring`), so the focus ring on the new `<button>` inherits the design system instead of a one-off hex.
